      "code": "{\"query\": \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR root cause analysis enterprise fix\", \"numResults\": 5}",
      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_efb903b876474a75abda2757d34811e4\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.remosoftware.com/info/fix-\",\n      \"title\": \"Fix WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR on Windows 10 and 11\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-02-07\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"[Troubleshooting](https://www.remosoftware.com/info/troubleshooting) , [Windows](https://www.remosoftware.com/info/windows)\\n\\n# How To Fix 0x00000124 Whea Uncorrectable Error on Windows?\\n\\n13 minutes read\\n\\nThe whea\\\\_uncorrectable\\\\_error is a type of blue screen error that indicates a major hardware issue on your Windows system. This error can be triggered by several factors like faulty RAM, overheating components, problematic hardware, outdated drivers, etc. This article will help you fix the Blue Screen of Death Error Code 0x00000124 WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR on Windows.\\n\\n* [Download Now For Windows](https://download.remosoftware.com/remo-recover-windows.exe)\\n* [Download Now For Mac](https://download.remosoftware.com/remo-recover-mac.zip)\\n\\nWritten By\\n\\n[John Harris](https://www.remosoftware.com/info/author/johnharris)\\n\\nUpdated On\\n\\nFebruary 7, 2025\\n\\nThe Windows Hardware Error Architecture, also known as WHEA. Display an error known as the whea\\\\_uncorrectable\\\\_error on a blue screen.\\nThis happens when your computer finds, identifies, and composes several diagnostic data and then automatically resets your Windows system. If the root problem or issue persists, your computer will crash or shut down after displaying the following WHEA uncorrectable error message.\\n\\nThe displayed message will probably look like this:\\n\\n* Your PC ran into a problem and needs to restart. We’re just collecting some error info, and then we’ll restart for you. If you’d like to know more, you can search online for this error: WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR.\\n* A problem has been detected, and Windows has been shut down to prevent damage to your computer.WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR.\\n\\nWindows stop code whea\\\\_uncorrectable\\\\_error is usually displayed at the time of blue screen crash; the whea error is mainly related to hardware issues, failing hardware devices, malfunctioning RAW or memory, driver problems, missing Windows OS updates, overclocking CPU and drivers, unexpected software conflicts, etc.\\nThe whea internal error indicates an issue with the hardware, and Windows OS cannot recover from it.\\n\\nI have tried various solutions; here’s a list of all the solutions that are guaranteed to fix the blue screen whea uncorrectable error.\\n\\n## How To Fix The Stop Code WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR on Windows 11 and 10 and Other Versions?\\n\\nBefore you proceed to fix the issue, Tech Experts like Imtiaz Hamid suggest users recover their data first; later on, they can go ahead and start troubleshooting the issue. Since this error can damage or erase the saved data.\\n\\nIf you have the latest backup of your important data, then you can skip this section and move ahead. But if you have not taken any prior backup, then you need to utilize any specialized data recovery tools like [Remo File Recovery Tool](https://www.remosoftware.com/remo-file-recovery-software) to help you [recover your files from your computer](https://www.remosoftware.com/computer-file-recovery) .\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.windowsmode.com/fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-windows\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR in Windows 10/11\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Most people solve it by Fix 2 or Fix 3. If your PC is overclocked, start with Fix 1 first.\\n\\nWhat This Error Means at a Glance\\n\\n* Windows detected an unrecoverable hardware error and forced a restart.\\n* Most common causes: overclocking, faulty RAM, bad device driver, or overheating CPU.\\n* Less common causes: failing hard drive or SSD, corrupted system files, bad Windows update.\\n* This is a hardware-level crash, not a typical app or software error.\\n* Affects Windows 10 and Windows 11. More common on overclocked or custom-built PCs.\\n\\nError Type\\n\\nBSOD / Hardware\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n\\nCPU / RAM / Driver\\n\\nAffects\\n\\nWindows 10 / 11\\n\\nDifficulty\\n\\nBeginner to advanced\\n\\nTime to Fix\\n\\n10 min – several hours\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* Video: How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR on Windows\\n* What Causes WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n* How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n* Quick Checklist: What to Try First\\n* Still Getting WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR? Advanced Steps\\n* Frequently Asked Questions\\n* Related Windows Error Fixes\\n\\n## Video: How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR on Windows\\n\\nWatch the full fix walkthrough for WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR on Windows 10 and 11, covering the overclocking reset, driver update, RAM test, and SFC repair steps shown below.\\n\\n## What Causes WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?\\n\\nThis error has more possible causes than most blue screens. Check the list below and pick the fix that best matches your situation before working through the numbered steps.\\n\\nOverclocking (Most Common)\\n\\nRunning your CPU, RAM, or GPU faster than stock speeds puts extra stress on the hardware. Even a previously stable overclock can cause this error after a Windows update, temperature spike, or power fluctuation.\\n\\nFaulty or Incompatible RAM\\n\\nBad memory is one of the top hardware causes. This includes physically failing RAM sticks, RAM running at the wrong speed for your motherboard, or mismatched sticks that are not compatible with each other.\\n\\nBad or Outdated Drivers\\nGPU drivers, chipset drivers, and storage controller drivers are the most common driver culprits. A buggy driver update can trigger this error even on hardware that was working fine the day before.\\n\\nOverheating CPU or GPU\\n\\nWhen a processor gets too hot, it can trigger hardware-level errors that cause this blue screen. Common on laptops with blocked vents, desktops with dried-out thermal paste, or rigs running demanding workloads in a hot room.\\n\\nFailing Hard Drive or SSD\\n\\nA drive that is starting to fail can trigger hardware errors as Windows tries to read or write to bad sectors. This is more common on older HDDs but can also happen with SSDs that are near end of life.\\n\\nCorrupted System Files\\n\\nA failed Windows update, a sudden shutdown during an update, or malware can corrupt core Windows files. This is less common than hardware causes but worth checking if all hardware tests come back clean.\\n\\n## How to Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\nWork through these fixes in order.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.thewindowsclub.com/whea_uncorrectable_error-0x00000124\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR 0x00000124 BSOD [Fix]\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-04-21\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"[TheWindowsClub Logo](https://www.thewindowsclub.com/)\\n\\nThe Windows Club\\n\\nTheWindowsClub covers authentic Windows 11, Windows 10 tips, tutorials, how-to's, features, freeware. Created by Anand Khanse, MVP.\\n\\nShow Search\\n\\nHide Search\\n\\n# WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR, 0x00000124 Blue Screen on Windows 11/10\\n\\n**[Download Windows Speedup Tool to fix errors and make PC run faster](https://reviews.thewindowsclub.com/recommends/fortectbfp/)**\\n\\nOne commonly faced Blue Screen error is **WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR** , **The system encountered an uncorrectable hardware** error, Code **0x00000124** . Based on the error data that is provided by the Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA), this bug check indicates that a fatal hardware error has occurred. It could be caused due to the RAM, Hard Drive, or any other hardware component. It is typically related to physical hardware failures. It can be heat-related, defective hardware, memory, or even a processor that is beginning to fail or has failed.\\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR, 0x00000124 Blue Screen on Windows 11/10\\n\\n## WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR 0x00000124 BSOD\\n\\nIf you receive this error, it means that a hardware error has occurred and that your PC has shut down suddenly to protect itself from data loss. The following potential fixes can be carried out to fix BSOD errors related to _WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR_ on Windows 11/10-\\n\\n1. Disable Overclocking if you have enabled it\\n2. Ensure that your computer’s cooling systems are working\\n3. Run Diagnostics to check the Memory\\n4. Update or Rollback Drivers.\\n5. Using System File Checker.\\n6. Disable Digital Driver Signature Enforcement.\\n\\nIf you tend to create a System Restore point usually, you can try to undo any modifications on your computer by [performing System Restore](https://www.thewindowsclub.com/create-system-restore-point) . Secondly, it is recommended that you carry out these tasks mentioned below in [Safe Mode with Networking](https://www.thewindowsclub.\\ncom/boot-windows-10-in-safe-mode) only.\\n\\n#### 1] Disable Overclocking if you have enabled it\\n\\nIf [Overclocking](https://www.thewindowsclub.com/is-pc-overclocking-really-worth-it) has been enabled, try disabling it. This should help.\\n\\n#### 2] Ensure that your computer’s cooling systems are working\\n\\nYou need to get your hardware opened and check if the computer’s cooling systems like fans, etc., are working normally.\\n\\n#### 3] Run system diagnostics\\n\\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR, 0x00000124 Blue Screen on Windows 11/10\\n\\nRun [Windows Memory Diagnostics Tool](https://www.thewindowsclub.com/windows-memory-diagnostics-tool-in-windows-7) to confirm that the system memory is not defective.\\n\\n#### 4] Update or Rollback Driver\\n\\nIt is less likely, but possible, that a driver is causing the hardware to fail. So, if you recently updated a driver, roll back. If you use an old device driver, see if updates are available.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://techlasi.com/pc/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\\n\\nBy [MK Usmaan](https://techlasi.com/author/mkusman22/ \\\"View all posts by MK Usmaan\\\") / February 12, 2026\\n\\nAre you facing the dreaded blue screen with a WHEA uncorrectable error message? You’re not alone. This frustrating hardware related error has troubled computer users for years, but with advances in diagnostic technology in 2026, we now have better solutions than ever before. This comprehensive guide will walk you through everything you need to know about WHEA errors, from understanding what they are to implementing the most effective fixes using the latest tools and techniques.\\n\\nWHEA Uncorrectable Error\\n\\n## **What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?**\\n\\nA WHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) uncorrectable error occurs when Windows detects a serious hardware problem that it cannot recover from automatically.\\nUnlike correctable hardware errors that Windows can resolve on the fly, uncorrectable errors force your system to shut down to prevent potential damage to your hardware or data corruption.\\n\\n### **Windows Hardware Error Architecture**\\n\\nWindows Hardware Error Architecture is a platform level error handling mechanism introduced in [Windows Vista](https://techlasi.com/savvy/windows-vs-linux-vs-macos/) that provides a standardized way for the operating system to handle hardware errors. WHEA improves upon the older Machine Check Architecture by offering enhanced error reporting and more detailed diagnostic information.\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n  \\n    + Windows Hardware Error Architecture\\n    + Common Error Codes Associated with WHEA Errors\\n* Primary Causes of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n  \\n    + Hardware Component Failures\\n    + Overclocking Issues\\n    + Driver and Firmware Problems\\n* Symptoms and Identification of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n+ Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) Appearances\\n    + Event Viewer Diagnostics\\n* Step-by-Step Troubleshooting Guide\\n  \\n    + Immediate Actions to Take\\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Procedures\\n    + Hardware Component Verification\\n* Prevention Strategies for WHEA Errors\\n  \\n    + Proper System Maintenance\\n    + Cooling Solutions and Temperature Management\\n    + Safe Overclocking Practices\\n* Recent Developments in WHEA Error Management\\n  \\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Tools\\n    + AI Assisted Troubleshooting\\n* Conclusion\\n* FAQs\\n  \\n    + Can software cause WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + How can I tell which hardware component is causing my WHEA error?\\n    + Are WHEA errors covered under warranty?\\n    + Can updating BIOS fix WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + Why do WHEA errors sometimes occur only during specific activities like gaming?\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ninjaone.com/blog/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-in-windows-11\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix \\\"WHEA_Uncorrectable_Error\\\" in Windows 11\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-24\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Home / Blog / IT Ops / How to Fix the WHEA\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error in Windows 11\\n\\nIT Ops\\n\\n/\\n\\n* Last updated February 24, 2026\\n\\n/\\n\\n* 6 min read\\n\\n# How to Fix the WHEA\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error in Windows 11\\n\\n* Picture of Mikhail Blacer Mikhail Blacer\\n\\nby Mikhail Blacer , IT Technical Writer\\n\\nHow to Fix the WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 11 blog banner image\\n\\nTable of contents\\n\\n## Instant Summary\\n\\nSummarize Blog\\n\\nThis NinjaOne blog post offers a comprehensive basic CMD commands list and deep dive into Windows commands with over 70 essential cmd commands for both beginners and advanced users. It explains practical command prompt commands for file management, directory navigation, network troubleshooting, disk operations, and automation with real examples to improve productivity. Whether you’re learning foundational cmd commands or mastering advanced Windows CLI tools, this guide helps you use the Command Prompt more effectively.\\n\\nFree Trial\\n\\n## Key Points\\n* Identify Faulting Hardware: Review WHEA-Logger events in Event Viewer to isolate CPU, memory, PCIe bus, or storage errors.\\n* Update BIOS/UEFI Firmware First: Install vendor-supported firmware updates to fix instability from outdated microcode, voltage control, or PCIe initialization.\\n* Run Targeted Hardware Diagnostics: Stress-test RAM, CPU, and storage using vendor tools or industry-standard diagnostics to confirm whether components fail under load.\\n* Update Chipset, Storage, and Device Drivers: Install the latest supported drivers to correct hardware signaling issues that may trigger repeated WHEA events.\\n* Validate Post-Repair Stability: Clear WHEA logs, apply stress tests, and monitor Event Viewer to ensure the system remains stable without recurring hardware faults.\\n\\nA WHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) Uncorrectable Error (or **whea\\\\_uncorrectable\\\\_error** ) occurs when hardware reports a fault via the WHEA system.\\nIt’s known as a blue screen of death (BSOD) error that comes from failing CPUs, unstable memory, PCIe bus issues, storage faults, or outdated firmware.\\n\\nThis guide delivers a workflow to fix a WHEA Uncorrectable Error. We’ll go through ways on how to identify the hardware source, run targeted diagnostics, update firmware, remove overclocking, and verify system stability.\\n\\n## Steps to fix the WHEA uncorrectable error\\n\\nTo stop the [WHEA uncorrectable error code](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/whea/introduction-to-the-windows-hardware-error-architecture) , you will need to perform hardware-focused troubleshooting. Before you go through the steps, you will need to confirm the following requirements:\\n\\n📌 **Prerequisites:**\\n\\n* You will need administrator access on the affected device.\\n* This requires you to enter BIOS or UEFI for firmware and stability changes.\\n* You will need to have tools for memory, CPU, and storage diagnostics.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://umatechnology.org/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide-for-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Check the drive’s SMART health with the manufacturer’s tool, update SSD firmware, reseat the drive if it is removable, and make sure it has adequate cooling. Back up files immediately if the drive reports media errors, critical warnings, or rapid health decline.\\n\\n### Should I update my BIOS or UEFI to fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nA BIOS/UEFI update can help if the problem is related to CPU microcode, memory compatibility, PCIe stability, or a newer processor installed on an older motherboard. Use the motherboard or laptop manufacturer’s exact model page, avoid beta firmware unless support recommends it, and do not interrupt the update. After updating, load optimized defaults before reapplying settings such as XMP, EXPO, undervolting, or fan curves.\\n\\n### Is it safe to keep using a PC that gets WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nOccasional crashes after a bad driver or unstable tuning may not mean immediate hardware failure, but repeated WHEA errors should not be ignored.\\nContinued use can risk data loss if the cause is storage failure, overheating, or unstable power. Back up your data first, remove overclocks, monitor temperatures, and stop heavy workloads until the system passes stability tests.\\n\\n## Bottom Line\\n\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error is usually a sign that Windows detected a serious hardware or low-level system stability problem, so the safest approach is to troubleshoot methodically: undo recent changes, check temperatures, update BIOS/UEFI and drivers, then test memory, storage, CPU, GPU, and power stability.\\n\\nIf the error continues after clean updates, safe settings, and component diagnostics, treat it as a likely failing part rather than a normal software crash. Back up data, stop overclocking, and consider professional testing or hardware replacement before the issue leads to data loss or an unbootable system.\\n\\n#### Quick Recap\\n\\nBestseller No. 1\\n\\n[Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.\\n1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09TL7K1TF?tag=umatechnology09-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=windows+recovery+software \\\"Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more\\\")\\n\\n[Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09TL7K1TF?tag=umatechnology09-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=windows+recovery+software \\\"Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more\\\")\\n\\nData recovery software for retrieving lost files; Easily recover documents, audios, videos, photos, images and e-mails\\n\\n$24.99\\n\\nBestseller No.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fastsoftwares.com/blog/whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"Fixing WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR: Expert Solutions fastsoftwares.com https://www.fastsoftwares.com › ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-05-06\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Skip to navigation Skip to content\\n\\n#### Browse\\n\\n* [My Account](https://www.fastsoftwares.com//my-account/)\\n* [Customer Help](https://www.fastsoftwares.com/help-center-3/)\\n\\n#### Got questions?\\n\\n[Email us: [email protected]](#)\\n\\n[Home](https://www.fastsoftwares.com) / [Blog](https://www.fastsoftwares.com/category/blog/) / Fixing WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR: Expert Solutions\\n\\n# **How Do I Fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR?**\\n\\nfastsoftwares how to fix whea uncorrectable error 01\\n\\nWHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR, also known as a “blue screen of death” (BSOD), is a serious error that occurs on Windows computers, indicating that a hardware problem has occurred and the system has been shut down to prevent further damage. If you’re dealing with this error, it can be a frustrating experience, and you may feel like giving up on your computer. But don’t despair!\\n\\nYou can solve the issue and get your computer operating again by following a few simple steps.\\nTo get you back to your work or leisure activities as soon as possible, we will show you the best options to fix the WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR in this guide. To resolve this issue, we will go over all the necessary details.\\n\\nIf you want to put an end to the frustration caused by this error, keep reading!\\n\\n## **What Is the WHEA Uncorrectable Error?**\\n\\nThis error, also known as stop code WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR or Windows code 0x0000124, is a hardware error. It indicates an issue with your computer’s hardware, such as your GPU, CPU, or RAM. The WHEA Uncorrectable Error message is also caused by voltage issues.\\n\\nThe most common causes for WHEA Uncorrectable Error are:\\n\\n* Malfunctioning hardware\\n* Driver compatibility problems\\n* Overclocking and overheating\\n* Corrupt system files or registry keys\\n* Voltage changes and issues\\n\\nBecause this error is hard to diagnose accurately, we recommend that you take a look at the automatically generated error dump file (.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://couldask.com/en/guides/tech/oswindows/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 10/11 — Step-by-Step Guide\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-06-27\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Sunday, June 28\\n\\nTheme\\n\\nEN ▾\\n\\n[Русский](https://couldask.com/ru/kak-ispravit-oshibku-whea-uncorrectable-error) [English](https://couldask.com/en/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error)\\n\\n🏠 Home Sections: All 📖 Guides 🔧 Fixes 💡 Concepts ⚖️ Compare 🛠️ Tools Справка\\n\\n×\\n\\n#### Help\\n\\nUse the search bar to find error codes or manuals. Articles are categorized in the top menu.\\n\\nSubcategories: Back All Adults Contact Excel Git Google Mail Media Windows More 7 ▾\\n\\n### Select Subcategory\\n\\n×\\n\\nHome / Guides / IT & Tech / Windows\\n\\nIT & Tech\\n\\n# How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 10/11\\n\\nCouldAsk Editorial 27\\\\.06.2026 2 min 👁️ 139\\n\\nQuick Solution\\n\\nError 0x00000124 is a critical hardware failure (overheating, overclocking, or power issues). Key steps: reset BIOS to factory defaults, disable overclocking, and check system files and disk integrity.\\nBlue screen of death with WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR and stop code 0x00000124 on a computer monitor The **WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR** (stop code `0x00000124` ) is a critical failure of the Windows Hardware Error Architecture. Unlike many other Blue Screen of Death (BSoD) errors, this one indicates a hardware issue in 90% of cases, rather than a software glitch.\\n\\n## Main Causes of the Error\\n\\nThe system protects itself to prevent physical damage to the components. The primary culprits are:\\n\\n* Overheating of the processor (CPU) or graphics card (GPU).\\n* Unstable overclocking or enabled XMP profiles for RAM.\\n* A faulty power supply unit (PSU) causing voltage spikes.\\n* Physical wear and tear of the system drive (SSD/HDD).\\n\\n## Step-by-Step Solution\\n\\n### Step 1: Disable Overclocking\\n\\nIf you have overclocked your CPU or RAM, revert to the base settings.\\n1\\\\. Restart your computer and enter the BIOS/UEFI (usually by pressing `Del` or `F2` ).\\n2\\\\.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.positioniseverything.net/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide-for-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* What the WHEA Uncorrectable Error Means in Windows\\n  \\n    + Where Windows records more detail\\n* Common Causes: Hardware Failure, Drivers, Overclocking, and Firmware\\n  \\n    + Hardware problems\\n    + Driver and Windows-level causes\\n    + Overclocking and aggressive performance settings\\n    + BIOS, UEFI, and firmware issues\\n* First Checks Before Advanced Troubleshooting\\n  \\n    + Record the stop code details and recent changes\\n    + Remove overclocks and performance tuning\\n    + Check physical connections, cooling, and power\\n* How to Diagnose CPU, RAM, GPU, and Storage Problems\\n  \\n    + CPU and motherboard checks\\n    + RAM testing\\n    + GPU and power-related testing\\n    + Storage and file system checks\\n* Driver, BIOS, and Windows Update Fixes\\n  \\n    + Update chipset, storage, GPU, and network drivers carefully\\n    + Check BIOS/UEFI updates and reset unstable firmware settings\\n    + Use Windows Update, optional updates, and system file repair\\n* When to Reset Settings, Replace Hardware, or Seek Repair\\n  \\n    + Reset firmware and performance settings first\\n    + Replace parts when failures follow the component\\n* Frequently Asked Questions\\n  \\n    + Can the WHEA Uncorrectable Error be caused by software, or is it always bad hardware?\\n    + What should I check first after getting a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n    + How do I know whether RAM, CPU, GPU, or storage is causing the crash?\\n    + Can XMP, EXPO, undervolting, or overclocking cause WHEA errors?\\n    + When should I replace hardware or take the PC to a repair shop?\\n* Bottom Line\\n\\n## What the WHEA Uncorrectable Error Means in Windows\\n\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error is a Windows blue screen stop error usually shown with the code **WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR** .\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fonelab.com/resource/crashed-windows-whea-uncorrectable-error-recovery.html\",\n      \"title\": \"Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error on Windows and Recover Data\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2022-11-28\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Guide List\\n\\n* Part 1. How to Fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error on Windows\\n* Part 2. How to Recover Data After WHEA Uncorrectable Error on Windows\\n* Part 3. FAQs about Recovering Data After WHEA Uncorrectable Error on Windows\\n\\nRecover PC Data Now\\n\\nRecover the lost/deleted data from computer, hard drive, flash drive, memory card, digital camera and more.\\n\\n[Free Download](https://download.fonelab.com/data-retriever.exe) [Free Download](https://download.fonelab.com/mac-data-retriever.dmg)\\n\\n# Recover Data After Fixing WHEA Uncorrectable Error on Windows\\n\\nUpdated by Lisa Ou / Nov 28, 2022 10:00\\n\\nWHEA Uncorrectable Error or Windows Hardware Error Architecture is a hardware error on the operating system. When you see this message on your computer's blue screen, it means a hardware component in your computer's operating system is malfunctioning. This is detected through the hardware's error detection mechanisms. Hence, it will know when a hardware error occurs.\\nThey can either be classified as corrected or uncorrected errors. When this happens, your computer shuts down instantly to protect itself against data loss.\\n\\nSeveral variables can cause this WHEA issue. One of the most common is due to hardware failure. This includes a faulty hard drive, memory, incorrectly positioned CPU, corrupted RAM, and more hardware issues that can lead to an uncorrectable error. Another is problems with drivers' compatibility and outdated Windows versions. It can affect the hardware to malfunction or work differently. Other possible factors could also include voltage problems, corrupted Windows system files, overclocking, driver conflicts, and more.\\n\\nWhile the mentioned issues above may lead to WHEA Uncorrectable Error, this error, on the other hand, may cause data loss. Even though the computer shuts down immediately, losing data is still possible with this issue. Hence, this article will present some reliable ways to fix the problem.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0d435344dffeUDWkqHfoow14g5\"\n}",
