      "type": "answer",
      "text": "**Enterprise Root Cause Analysis: WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR**\n\n**Root Cause Summary:**\nThis BSOD indicates a fatal hardware error detected by Windows Hardware Error Architecture (WHEA). In 90% of cases, it's hardware-related. Most likely causes (ordered by probability):\n1. **Overclocking/Undervolting** (CPU/RAM/GPU unstable settings)\n2. **Overheating** (CPU/GPU thermal throttling failure)\n3. **Faulty RAM** (memory module degradation)\n4. **Driver conflict** (especially GPU/chipset/storage drivers)\n5. **Failing storage** (SSD/HDD bad sectors)\n6. **Power supply instability** (voltage spikes/drops)\n\n**Fixability Score: 7/10**\n- **Software/driver issues:** Highly fixable (9/10) via updates/rollback\n- **Overclocking instability:** Fixable (8/10) by resetting BIOS\n- **Overheating:** Moderate (6/10) with cooling improvements\n- **Hardware failure:** Low (3/10) requiring component replacement\n\n**Reliability of Fix:**\n- **High** if cause is driver/software (updates resolve)\n- **Medium** if cause is overclocking/thermal (may recur under load)\n- **Low** if cause is failing hardware (replacement needed)\n\n**Temperature Improvement Assessment:**\nYou can safely monitor temperatures without stress testing:\n- **PowerShell (no install):**\n  ```powershell\n  Get-WmiObject MSAcpi_ThermalZoneTemperature -Namespace \"root/wmi\" | Select CurrentTemperature\n  ```\n  (Note: Returns tenths of Kelvin; subtract 2732 for Celsius)\n\n- **Python (using `psutil`):**\n  ```python\n  import psutil\n  print(psutil.sensors_temperatures())\n  ```\n  Install with: `pip install psutil`\n\n**Component Health Check (Non-Stress):**\n1. **Event Viewer:** Check for WHEA-Logger events (Event ID 1, 17, 18)\n2. **Windows Memory Diagnostic:** Run `mdsched.exe` (basic RAM check)\n3. **SFC/SCANNOW:** `sfc /scannow` (system file integrity)\n4. **CrystalDiskInfo:** Check SSD/HDD SMART health\n5. **HWMonitor:** Monitor idle/load temperatures\n\n**Immediate Actions:**\n1. Reset BIOS to defaults (disable XMP/overclock)\n2. Update GPU/chipset drivers\n3. Clean dust from heatsinks/fans\n4. Run `mdsched.exe` for memory check\n\n**Bottom Line:** The error is likely fixable without hardware replacement if you've recently changed settings or drivers. Monitor temperatures with PowerShell/Python tools to identify thermal issues. If crashes persist after software fixes, consider professional hardware diagnostics.",
      "timestamp": 1783146335638
